      },
      "date": "2013-04-15 16:48:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI don't understand why class_export_rpc_get/put where changed to just counter inc/dec. It is not needed for export change, is it?\n\nthis can break obd_exports_barrier logic as exports will be moved to zombie list having requests in process.  Can we keep old logic when requests take export reference along with counter increment?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "42eaf8afd3854ba8a306caca2eff7a296720a786",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 212,
        "name": "Alexander Boyko",
        "email": "alexander.boyko@hpe.com",
        "username": "aboyko"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-15 19:33:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n>this can break obd_exports_barrier logic as exports will be moved to zombie list having requests in process. Can we keep old logic when requests take export reference along with counter increment?\n\nI don`t think so, the main export reference for request take at ptlrpc_handle_req_in()->class_conn2export(), and release at ptlrpc_server_drop_request(). So your example is not valid. Taking reference at class_export_rpc_get is unneeded.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
