      },
      "date": "2013-04-16 10:21:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nTwo test in sanity failed.\n\n56w failed according to low memory\n/usr/bin/lfs find -stripe_count 7 -type f /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56w |\n         /usr/bin/lfs_migrate -y -c 6\nerror: cb_find_init: lstat failedfor /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56w/file1: Cannot allocate memory (12)\nerror: find failed for /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56w.\n\n65ic failed \n\n05:30:50:LustreError: 11-0: lustre-OST0005-osc-ffff88007c992800: Communicating with 10.10.4.212@tcp, operation ldlm_enqueue failed with -12.\n05:30:50:LustreError: Skipped 5 previous similar messages\n05:30:50:Lustre: DEBUG MARKER: /usr/sbin/lctl mark  sanity test_65ic: @@@@@@ FAIL: find \\/mnt\\/lustre failed \n\nSo, I think, this faults doesn`t relate to this patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a80aba7b524193a63ececc652a79a94a7fb2cbd7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-16 12:47:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)\n\nI know that this functions were added when request was copied for recovery, so it had to take extra reference, probably this is not needed now. Anyway I am strongly disagree with adding in patch extra code without mentioning that in description, without explanation why it was done. \nSee inline comment, if you are still going to reduce number of references then fix that, so rpc counter will be equal to the number of references taken by this request, no need to just increase/decrease rpc counter if reference is not changed.  Also add description in patch comment, please.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "d17ff3d280da002b05f5b62e85103a229f05778a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 135,
        "name": "Vitaly Fertman",
        "email": "vitaly.fertman@hpe.com",
        "username": "vitaly_fertman"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-16 22:40:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (2 inline comments)\n\n> See inline comment, if you are still going to reduce number of references\n> then fix that, so rpc counter will be equal to the number of references\n> taken by this request, no need to just increase/decrease rpc counter if\n> reference is not changed. \n\nthis is not so for a long time (if not always) because request took a reference for export and later another reference for processing time along with rpc_count. in fact, no need for another reference. see inline comment.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "17d43d6b540a7104cf0cfbe8672c9464f1a404e4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-17 06:04:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (6 inline comments)\n\ncheck inlines, I make comments where it is OK and where inc/dec is not needed. So we have always reference change along with rpc count change, that is why I'd like to keep those changes in single function but not separated - just to make it clear - they must change together. Otherwise someday someone may forget to call class_export_rpc_inc() or call it without taking reference, breaking its consistence.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "e1822984b0828e1448c741502b44e98fda7abab3",
      "author": {
